Some Lipsey Exclusive guns happen fairly fast, others take some time. The Bearcat Shopkeeper is one gun that has been on the drawing table for several years. It all started with a visit by Lipsey to one of our biggest and most loyal dealers in Alabama. He showed them a beautiful little 3" barreled Ruger Bearcat. Everyone agreed it would make for a great Lipsey's Exclusive, and after talking to Ruger, they agreed to take a look at it. 
  Ruger decided to produce a round butt or birdshead type frame to go along with the 3" barrel. In addition to the 3" barrel and birdshead gripframe, they had to use a couple of other unique features to make it all work. Due to the short barrel, Ruger had to use a "button head" cylinder pin and a crescent shape ejector rod so that the spent cases could easily be extracted from the cylinder. Ruger is also using a steel ejector rod housing that matches the rest of the gun verses the aluminum one used on the standard Bearcats.
  Even though it took 3 years, the wonderful engineers at Ruger made it happen and now we have a true "Shopkeeper" size Ruger Bearcat. 
 This is one of those guns that once you put it in your hands, you will have to get one.

title: For Sale:  Complete Bedside Holster and CCW Rig for Glock 17/19/22/23
postcontent:
This listing is for a very comfortable, and concealable IWB Appendix Carry, custom, compact Kydex holster for Glock 17/19/22/23 and Complete Bedside Rig. 

We designed this bedside rig to allow our customers the all in one solution to transitioning from your everyday carry IWB holster to your "Sleepy Time" holster. No need to change holsters with our rigs! Simply take the weapon and holster off your belt at night and attach your holster to the bedside rig and always be prepared!

We at SSXHolsters take the following steps in creating each holster: 
First, we thermo-form our high quality .060 and .125 Kydex to the maximum pliability gradually, and without scorching the material with direct advice from the plastics industry leaders.    
Second, we hand press each holster up to 1200 lbs. psi. 
Third, we mill the holsters into the models shape/design, machine buff, then wet sand all edges to a nice smooth matte finish. 
All IWB holsters are fitted with a high quality metal belt clip attached at a single point with quality hardware and Loctite to provide a permanent bond while being forgiving of various body positions increasing comfort and ultimately more good people legally carrying their firearms on an everyday basis.  

Our Bedside Rigs are made of very high quality .125 Kydex with .125 ABS as the "under the mattress arm". This, combined with high quality hardware and absolute versatility gives us the confidence to say this is the best bedside/holster rig available!

Don't waste your money on the rest, spent it on the best!  

If there is ever an issue with your holster simply contact us with the information we provide with each shipment and we will either inform you how to address the issue easily, or we will fix it for you. We ask only that you pay return shipping. 

Why Kydex as opposed to other holster materials? 

Kydex®

KYDEX® (ACRYLIC/PVC ALLOY) SHEET

KYDEX® sheet is an extremely durable acrylic/PVC alloy extruded in a range of colors, patterns, textures, thicknesses, and grades to optimize long-term performance, appearance, and cost effectiveness across demanding and diverse end-use applications. Specialized grades of KYDEX® sheet are offered to satisfy requirements specific to thermoforming, membrane pressing, post-forming, brake-forming, and laminating, and to fit a broad range of specialized applications ranging from medical equipment housings and aircraft tray tables to retail store fixtures and trade show displays.

IMPACT RESISTANCE
No other thermoplastic sheet stands up to impact, and gouging like KYDEX® sheet. Depending on grade, KYDEX® sheet offers Notched Izod impact resistance to 18 ft-lbs/in., and is available in thicknesses from .028 to .500 inch to withstand levels of abuse from moderate to extreme. Due to its high degree of toughness and resilience, KYDEX® sheet can also be stretched at room temperature to twice its original dimension without breaking.



FLAME RETARDANCY
Depending on grade, KYDEX® sheet is available with fire ratings of UL Std. 94 V-0, UL Std. 94 5V; FAR 25.853 (a) and (d); FSTratings: ABD6031 D6-51377:FMVSS 302; Class I/A and others as described in the following pages.











CHEMICAL RESISTANCE
From sulfuric acid to brake fluid to carbon tetrachloride, high performance grades of KYDEX® sheet acrylic/PVC alloys are more resistant to a wider range of concentrated chemicals than any other thermoplastic. In fact, KYDEX® sheet meets the highest standards of chemical resistance for thermoplastic materials as defined inASTM D-1784 standard for Class 12454-C rigid polyvinyl chloride.



DIMENSIONAL STABILITY

title: For Sale:  Pedersoli 1874 Sharps Competition 45-70
postcontent:
With some hesitation, I am offering my Pedersoli 1874 Sharps Competition 45-70. I bought this rifle new in 2005 and have given it all the TLC it deserves in the years since. The rifle has not been altered in anyway. Included is a Lee Shaver mid-range Soule sight with Hadley eyecup. Original rear flip-up sight and front globe sight are also included. About 500 rounds have passed through this rifle, the first 50 of which were modern copper-jacketed bullets loaded over smokeless powder. The remaining rounds were cast lead over black powder. She shoots great with cloverleaf groups of three at 100 yards common if you do your job. I have used this rifle in several silhouette matches out to 500 yds and did well enough to hold my interest, though any lack of better scores was entirely my fault. She loves 535 gr. Postell bullets loaded to touching the lands (Pedersolis have a longer throat so a drive band and a half are exposed.). I never sized my brass nor crimped the bullets in. She is a heavy rifle at about 13 lbs. There is nary a mark on her as you can see in the photos. More photos available at:

http://s698.photobucket.com/user/cjkosti...REDACTED85164

The only reason I have decided to part with this rifle is I picked up a Browning Highwall BPCR in 45-70 and a C. Sharps 1874 in 45-100. It makes no sense to me to let this fine rifle sit in the safe.

PRICE: $1600.00 shipped in ConUS.
